## Recommended root cause (one sentence)

**At first PPEM draw, `ShaderImplementationPassPixelShaderProgram::m_graphicsData` for `2d_texture`’s pixel program is a non-null dangling pointer (very likely to a freed `Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData` block at `0x21250000` that was reused/overlaid with program/CrcString memory); `StaticShaderData::construct` and `apply` both read that engine value faithfully, so the Plan 17-03 `getReflectedCbufferLayouts()` loop walks garbage (`begin=0x1`).** The falsified “stale StaticShaderData snapshot vs recreated PS-data” theory does not match `snapshot == live`.

